RACE.FOOTNOTES: PUNCTUALITY tracked outside of the top pair and from the four path, bid leaving the three furlong pole, assumed command turning for home and drew off under moderate urging. ALPHA LEA got tangled up in the gate before leaving many lengths behind the rest of the field and lagged well behind throughout. FOLLOWING A STEWARDS' INQUIRY REVIEWING THE START, ALPHA LEA WAS FOUND TO HAVE BEEN GIVEN A FAIR START; THEREFORE NO CHANGE WAS MADE TO THE ORIGINAL ORDER OF FINISH.
